# Noctis Docker Compose Environment Variables
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# This file is for Docker Compose ONLY. The Noctis application itself uses
# a JSON config file pointed to by the NOCTIS_CONFIG environment variable.
# Copy this file to .env and fill in required values before running:
#
#   cp .env.example .env
#   docker compose up -d
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ── Required ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Master key for Meilisearch (required when using the 'search' profile).
# Generate with: openssl rand -hex 32
MEILI_MASTER_KEY=

# ── Optional: Image overrides ──────────────────────────────────────────────
# Override the Noctis server container image (default: stable from GHCR)
# NOCTIS_SERVER_IMAGE=ghcr.io/noctisapp/noctis-server:stable

# ── Optional: Port overrides ──────────────────────────────────────────────
# Port the Noctis HTTP server listens on (default: 8080)
# NOCTIS_HTTP_PORT=8080

# Port for Meilisearch search engine (default: 7700)
# MEILI_PORT=7700

# Port for Elasticsearch (default: 9200)
# ELASTICSEARCH_PORT=9200

# Port for LiveKit voice server (default: 7880)
# LIVEKIT_PORT=7880

# ── Notes ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# The application JSON config (NOCTIS_CONFIG) contains all other settings:
#   - database backend (sqlite / cassandra)
#   - Redis/Valkey connection string (internal.kv)
#   - S3/object storage credentials (s3.*)
#   - SMTP email settings (integrations.email.*)
#   - LiveKit API keys (integrations.voice.*)
#   - VAPID push notification keys (auth.vapid.*)
#   - Domain configuration (domain.*)
#
# For local development, copy config/config.dev.template.json to
# config/config.json, then run: bash scripts/dev_bootstrap.sh
# This will auto-generate all required secrets locally.
